Jonathan Matas' Porsche 911: "Document Of Energy"
Mark Zuckerberg was invited
Come by and check out Jonathan Matas' newest work: a Porsche 911 Art Car entitled "Document Of Energy: The Immeasurable Display of Phenomena". The car is here for everyone to see for the first time this weekend. Jonathan will be there to answer questions, talk about the creative process and discuss art- his favorite subject. The car was painted over the course of a month and a half, in several locations including Heron Arts in San Francisco, a Vacaville Garage, and a Santa Cruz front yard. It contains seas of detail and transparent and opaque layers of enamel paint, unlike any art car seen in the past ... It's a one of a kind piece that has to be experienced in person! We'll be hanging out in front of Jonathan's Mural on 741 Valencia, (next door to Tacolicious). Come by and say hi. We might even paint a few canvases. Half of the proceeds from the sale of this car will go to an amazing charity called Watsi, which helps crowdfund for surgeries for those in need all over the world. (http://www.watsi.org/) Special thanks to everyone that helped make this happen: Heron Arts Alexander Soufi Basil D Soufi Mark Slee Grace Garey Antonia Miano Yasmin Syed

FB AIR Season II Catalog Release Party
Mark Zuckerberg was invited
We are pleased to celebrate the release of this book cataloging our second season of artists in residence at Facebook. This publication documents the residencies of Jane Kim, Paul Morgan, Jessalyn Aaland, Val Britton, Stefanie Posavec, Barbara Holmes, Jeff Canham, Chris Duncan, Tucker Nichols, and Kelly Ording. We look forward to celebrating this great artists at the wonderful Park Life Gallery in the Mission. Books will be sold at a sliding scale of $20-40, all proceeds go to The Headlands Center for the Arts.

Unplug SF - Device Free Drinks IV (Free DIGITAL DETOX event)
Mark Zuckerberg was invited
An off-the-grid party to celebrate the National Day of Unplugging! UNPLUG! Please RSVP at http://unplugsf.eventbrite.com/ Check your phone at the door and together we’ll redefine what it means to truly be connected. Live Music by Mana Maddy, Billy Mickelson of 'Third Seven', Cello Joe, and a gypsy jazz group with a Violinist/Drummer/Clarinet/Accordion awesomeness... Vinyl DJ Set by The Handsome Young Men. Join us and our friends from Reboot, Inner Mission SF, Treehouse and yerdle for our largest Device-Free Drinks celebration to date. Leave your phone at home or check it at the door for a night of Digital Detox goodness - massage lounge, live music, typewriters, arts and crafts, hand-drawn portraits, board games, dancing... you name it! Unplug after a busy week and take time off the grid to feel awesome. - The Digital Detox Phone-Check at the Door (you can do it!) - Specialty Organic Concoctions - Wellness Lounge with Massage and Bodywork - Tea Lounge - Analog zone with Typewriters - Art Gallery - Crafts + Bracelet Making - Board Games and Cards - Herbal Drinks + Kombucha - Communal Art - Free Live Hand-Drawn Portraits - Live Music - Vinyl DJ’s spinning motown, soul and oldies - Guest Speakers - Gift Exchange with Yerdle - Conversation Prompts Ditch the Facebook status or checking-in with people on Instagram - be spontaneous and meet new people, play games, create art and celebrate community. Yerdle will be hosting a free sharing gift exchange. Bring something you already have as a gift to share and receive a $0.00 price tag redeemable for someone else's gift. You can also earn a $0.00 price tag by bringing something to give away. POST YOUR PHOTOS of what you'll be bringing here with a link to you item on Yerdle - http://www.yerdle.com. Guests will also receive a free month of Treehouse for unplugging. In collaboration with Treehouse and Reboot. --------- Digital Detox is an organization dedicated to finding, exploring and creating balance in the digital age. They host events and tech-free retreats where attendees disconnect from technology to reconnect with themselves, others and the world around them. Learn more about their retreats at TheDigitalDetox.org yerdle is a brand new SF start up that helps people share things with their friends for free. Just like we live in a hype-digital world, we also live in hyper-consumption world. The digital detox and yerdle are ways to combat this and return to a life of value and purpose. yerdle.com The National Day of Unplugging (NDU) is a project of Reboot, a national nonprofit that seeks to reinvent and reinvigorate Jewish traditions to make them resonate with a new generation. The NDU is in its fourth year and encourages people to take a regular pause from technology to reconnect with the community and those around them. NationalDayofUnplugging.com

Tutu Tuesday 4 Year Anniversary featuring House-Heads
Mark Zuckerberg was invited
For the 4 year anniversary of Tutu Tuesday, we are proud to welcome the long-anticipated debut of the House-Heads. This trio of music savvy savages is composed of tutu resident Atish, Roddy "The Ride" and Mark Slee, the lights/magic innovator behind the awe inspiring visual art installation now featured at 222. Close friends since college, the House-Heads have a palpable chemistry that fuels their spontaneous tag team sets. Tonight the guys will bring some special love to the decks will a tropical tutu theme featuring feathers and flamboyance. Guests are encouraged to don colorful resort wear and take a sweet 5 hour vacation from their workweek. One can do plenty but toucan do more! Bring a friend don't forget your camera...this will be a night tu remember. $7 or $2 in a tutu before midnight 22+ 22 handmade tutus for sale

Mark went
